1. What Photolithography Actually Does

In chip fabrication, a patterned mask and optics focus light onto a surface coated with photoresist.

The light exposes certain areas, which then get chemically developed to form structures.

So the process is:

pattern
   ↓
lens
   ↓
light projection
   ↓
etched structure

Ideas become physical geometry.

⸻

